WEBVTT

00:04.281 --> 00:06.349
This is, like,
the tenth meal out this week.

00:06.351 --> 00:07.817
Hey.

00:07.819 --> 00:09.653
Tomorrow, we cook.

00:09.655 --> 00:10.787
You say that every night.

00:10.789 --> 00:13.056
I'm sorry, sir.
Your card's been declined.

00:13.058 --> 00:15.525
That's got to be a mistake.

00:15.527 --> 00:16.493
I...

00:16.495 --> 00:17.594
They must have, changed

00:17.596 --> 00:19.095
the due date.

00:19.097 --> 00:20.730
Keep the change.

00:21.565 --> 00:23.800
Are we broke?

00:23.802 --> 00:25.368
No, we're not broke.

00:25.370 --> 00:26.536
And do you mind

00:26.538 --> 00:29.472
not announcing it to the
whole restaurant, please?

00:29.474 --> 00:30.840
Just not used to managing

00:30.842 --> 00:32.142
the bills

00:32.144 --> 00:33.777
and working and all that stuff.

00:33.779 --> 00:35.078
That used to be Mom's job?

00:35.080 --> 00:36.346
Yes. And now it's my job,

00:36.348 --> 00:37.647
and I have it under control.

00:37.649 --> 00:38.682
You know you can

00:38.684 --> 00:40.116
set that stuff up
automatically now?

00:40.118 --> 00:41.284
Like, online.

00:41.286 --> 00:42.419
Like most young people do.

00:42.421 --> 00:44.254
Yes, I know.

00:44.256 --> 00:46.389
Let's go.

00:46.391 --> 00:49.759
You gonna be able to pay
for my college, Dad?

00:49.761 --> 00:51.528
You can go
to any college you want to.

00:51.530 --> 00:52.495
As long as your brother and I

00:52.497 --> 00:54.130
- can come for a sleepover.
- Yep.

00:54.132 --> 00:55.665
No way, you guys. Not happening.

00:55.667 --> 00:57.967
Don't worry about money.
Come on.

01:00.771 --> 01:01.971
Here's the coffee machine.

01:01.973 --> 01:03.873
Okay.
Make sure this red light is off.

01:03.875 --> 01:05.542
- Mr. Jones will notice.
- Sure.

01:06.978 --> 01:08.478
And turn off your phone. Sorry.

01:08.480 --> 01:09.679
I thought it was on silent.

01:09.681 --> 01:10.847
Good morning, everybody.

01:10.849 --> 01:12.716
Hey, Mr. Jones.
Good morning, Mr. Jones.

01:12.718 --> 01:14.150
You must be the new intern.

01:14.152 --> 01:15.652
Miss Boyle.

01:15.654 --> 01:17.987
Hi, Mr. Jones. Yes, I'm Nicky.

01:17.989 --> 01:19.856
Come on,
let's chat for a minute.

01:21.659 --> 01:24.761
I hope Grace showed you
the time of your life

01:24.763 --> 01:26.463
on the tour
of the coffee machine.

01:26.465 --> 01:28.331
She did, Mr. Jones. Thank you.

01:28.333 --> 01:30.667
Free coffee all day long.

01:30.669 --> 01:33.269
Doughnuts, too.
Cake on birthdays.

01:33.271 --> 01:35.839
We're basically the
Google offices...

01:35.841 --> 01:38.208
Minus the pingpong tables,

01:38.210 --> 01:40.944
stock options, big salaries.

01:40.946 --> 01:42.378
Really hope you didn't come here
to get rich.

01:42.380 --> 01:45.882
Nope, just a really big fan
of what you do.

01:45.884 --> 01:47.317
And now starting your own

01:47.319 --> 01:49.819
refugee organization, it's...

01:49.821 --> 01:52.021
really inspiring, Mr. Jones.

01:52.023 --> 01:54.090
"It's really inspiring, Bobby."

01:54.092 --> 01:55.592
So...

01:55.594 --> 01:57.427
what inspires you?

01:57.429 --> 01:58.762
What are your interests?

01:58.764 --> 02:01.097
I like to read.

02:01.099 --> 02:02.699
Go to art museums.

02:02.701 --> 02:04.234
Do you really like
to go to art museums,

02:04.236 --> 02:06.369
or do you just think
it makes you sound cultured?

02:06.371 --> 02:08.604
6040?

02:08.607 --> 02:10.173
Honest answer. I like it.

02:10.175 --> 02:11.908
- Thank you.
- And I can see

02:11.910 --> 02:13.309
you have a nice sense of style.

02:13.311 --> 02:15.512
That shirt is...

02:15.514 --> 02:16.913
Stella McCartney?

02:16.915 --> 02:19.015
I wish.

02:19.017 --> 02:20.750
Well, you wear it well,
Nicky Boyle.

02:22.087 --> 02:24.754
Now go get some work done.

02:24.756 --> 02:27.423
Thank you.

02:32.930 --> 02:34.931
Sir!

02:34.933 --> 02:36.032
Sir, excuse me?

02:36.034 --> 02:38.434
Yeah, I'm talking to you.

02:38.436 --> 02:40.270
Stop for a sec, please.

02:41.639 --> 02:43.473
Identification, please.

02:43.475 --> 02:45.141
I wasn't doing anything wrong.

02:45.143 --> 02:46.442
Saw you jaywalking over there.

02:46.444 --> 02:48.077
You're charging me
for jaywalking?

02:48.079 --> 02:49.279
I'm not charging you
with anything.

02:49.281 --> 02:50.513
Then I don't owe you anything.

02:50.515 --> 02:51.948
Excuse me, sir?

02:51.950 --> 02:53.483
Hey, stop! Now.

02:53.485 --> 02:56.352
Stop!

02:56.354 --> 02:58.755
Sir, what are you doing
in this neighborhood?

02:58.757 --> 03:01.324
I don't owe you an explanation.

03:03.828 --> 03:06.496
Sir, please take your hands
out of your pockets.

03:08.165 --> 03:10.466
Take your hands
out of your pockets now.

03:12.270 --> 03:14.504
Do you not have
identification, sir?

03:14.506 --> 03:15.738
He didn't do anything wrong.

03:15.740 --> 03:16.940
Take a step back.
The man has rights,

03:16.942 --> 03:18.374
officer.
Take a step back, everybody.

03:18.376 --> 03:19.776
Take a step back, sir.

03:19.778 --> 03:21.077
I'm just asking for this man's
ID, all right, folks?

03:21.079 --> 03:22.178
Thank you.

03:22.180 --> 03:24.747
Are you refusing
to show identification, sir?

03:24.749 --> 03:26.749
Do you not have identification?

03:26.751 --> 03:27.750
What do you think you're doing?

03:27.752 --> 03:29.285
Sir, are you
an illegal immigrant?

03:29.287 --> 03:31.721
- That's racial profiling.
- Whoa.

03:31.723 --> 03:32.922
Take a step back.

03:32.924 --> 03:34.824
Take a step back.

03:34.826 --> 03:36.025
Sir, I need you
to back all the way up.

03:36.027 --> 03:36.860
All right, you can't...

03:36.862 --> 03:37.961
That's harassment.

03:37.963 --> 03:39.295
All right, ma'am, back up.

03:39.297 --> 03:41.497
- Back up, everybody. Back up!
- Get her badge number.

03:41.499 --> 03:43.466
You need to... Sir, I need you
to back up now.

03:43.468 --> 03:46.603
Sir, I need you
to take a step back right now.

03:46.605 --> 03:48.371
I hear you, but please

03:48.373 --> 03:51.374
take a step back and listen.

03:54.879 --> 03:57.780
So, convince me.

03:57.782 --> 04:00.116
That little gem
set us back a couple years.

04:00.118 --> 04:01.217
- In what way?
- In terms

04:01.219 --> 04:02.418
of our socalled
"community policing."

04:02.420 --> 04:03.519
Not "socalled."

04:03.521 --> 04:04.921
It is when that's
the how to video.

04:04.923 --> 04:06.356
All I see is a cop

04:06.358 --> 04:07.523
doing her job.

04:07.525 --> 04:08.791
All you see is what
you want to see, then.

04:08.793 --> 04:09.859
The officer stopped

04:09.861 --> 04:11.194
and questioned the guy,

04:11.196 --> 04:12.929
and the guy refused
to give his ID.

04:12.931 --> 04:14.530
They're both within
their rights.

04:14.532 --> 04:16.031
- Exactly.
- Back in the day,

04:16.034 --> 04:17.901
- yes. Today, no.
- How?

04:17.903 --> 04:18.834
The governor's

04:18.837 --> 04:21.170
executive order
specifically bars

04:21.172 --> 04:24.474
state agencies from asking
a person's immigration status.

04:24.476 --> 04:26.075
Except in certain situations,

04:26.077 --> 04:27.810
such as a law enforcement
investigation.

04:27.812 --> 04:29.512
We all read the order.

04:29.514 --> 04:31.581
That isn't exactly
a law enforcement investigation.

04:31.583 --> 04:32.582
Well, some clips show

04:32.584 --> 04:35.084
Rivera jaywalking.
Which isn't a crime.

04:35.086 --> 04:36.386
But is illegal.

04:36.388 --> 04:38.054
What it says is jaywalking

04:38.056 --> 04:40.456
is a crime that gets you
thrown out of the country

04:40.458 --> 04:43.359
if you look
like Mr. Rivera there.

04:44.194 --> 04:46.529
Why all the hype, Garrett?

04:46.531 --> 04:47.730
It's not hype.

04:47.732 --> 04:49.165
When these videos went viral,

04:49.167 --> 04:50.600
Immigration and Customs

04:50.602 --> 04:52.435
tracked him down.

04:52.437 --> 04:53.836
He's here illegally.

04:53.838 --> 04:55.405
Then all's well that ends well.

04:55.407 --> 04:57.206
Sometimes I just want
to clock you, you know that?

04:57.208 --> 04:59.609
What?
The guy's got a clean record,

04:59.611 --> 05:01.644
a steady job, a wife,

05:01.646 --> 05:03.379
two kids and a newborn.

05:03.381 --> 05:07.083
And thanks to our eager and
industrious young officer,

05:07.085 --> 05:08.418
he's now awaiting trial

05:08.420 --> 05:11.321
for deportation
back to Venezuela.

05:11.323 --> 05:14.524
Look at it that way,
guess it gets a little muddy.

05:14.526 --> 05:16.092
Out there, in this community?

05:16.094 --> 05:17.260
It's not muddy at all.

05:17.262 --> 05:19.162
It's gin clear.

05:19.164 --> 05:21.731
Our community policing
is a scam.

05:23.600 --> 05:26.936
You need to tread lightly there.

05:29.374 --> 05:32.442
I flog our progress
relentlessly and proudly

05:32.444 --> 05:35.611
eight days a week,
but not for this.

05:39.683 --> 05:41.384
We need to own up to it,

05:41.386 --> 05:43.453
loud and clear,

05:43.455 --> 05:46.456
if you want to gain back
the lost ground.

05:53.531 --> 05:56.032
- What do we got?
- Detectives.

05:56.034 --> 05:57.633
Victim is Bruce Daniels.

05:57.635 --> 05:59.669
50s. Owner of the apartment.

05:59.671 --> 06:02.005
He was discovered this morning
by his neighbors.

06:02.007 --> 06:03.773
Any sign of forced entry?

06:03.775 --> 06:05.174
Nah, not so far.

06:05.176 --> 06:07.176
For sure, no obvious ones.

06:07.178 --> 06:09.245
Where is he? Right this way.

